  "texts": [
    "By assuming that terms with similar words before and after are semantically similar, embedding models learn vector representations of the words and their average contexts.",
    "In this way, distances between words in a continuous vector (measured by cosine similarity for example), indicate how similar the words are expected to be in their linguistic meaning (i.e., how replaceable one word might be with another).NLP has seen a revolution starting with the incorporation of neural network based models in the 2010s, and with the development of new ways to represent text [30] that work well with deep learning methods [31,32].",
    "Deep learning is now ubiquitous in NLP research, often superseding traditional NLP pipelines [33].",
    "Various deep neural network (DNN) architectures have been used to address NLP tasks including convolutional neural networks (CNN), recurrent neural networks -most famously represented by the Long-Short Term Memory (LSTM) and the Bi-directional LSTM models -and graph neural networks [34].",
    "Similar to first generation neural language models (word2vec, GloVe), these DNN-based models aim to produce meaningful word embeddings."
  ],
